name: soy-based resin production | polyester resin, unsaturated | Cutoff, S
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/5297/documentation

This dataset represents the production of soy-based resin from refined soybean oil. 

From reception of refined soybean oil and other raw materials at the factory gate through production of soy resin. From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities.

The dataset does not include shipping to customers. System boundary is at the resin plant.
category: C:Manufacturing/20:Manufacture of chemicals and chemical products/201:Manufacture of basic chemicals, fertilizers and nitrogen compounds, plastics/2013:Manufacture of plastics and synthetic rubber in primary forms

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data collected from a manufacturer in the U.S.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Process description: resin produced by reacting refined soybean oil, ethanol, and other materials.  Water and ethanol distillates produced in the process are burned through an oxidizer. The activity ends with the reacted resin being diluted in styrene to produce the mixture, ready to be shipped to customers.  Current technology for one manufacturer; unknown how representative this product is amongst all soy resins.;of this nature available in the marketplace.

exchanges.description: Biobased resin that can be used interchangeably with non-biobased resins.
